{"title_page": "1996\u201397 Macedonian First Football League", "text_new": "{{Infobox football league season\n| competition      = Macedonian First League\n| season           = 1996\u201397\n| winners          = [[FK Sileks|Sileks]]<br />2nd domestic title\n| relegated        = [[KF Shk\u00ebndija|Shk\u00ebndija]]<br />[[FK Rudar Probi\u0161tip|Rudar]]\n| continentalcup1  = [[1997\u201398 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]]\n| continentalcup1 qualifiers = [[FK Sileks|Sileks]]\n| continentalcup2  = [[1997\u201398 UEFA Cup Winners' Cup|Cup Winners' Cup]]\n| continentalcup2 qualifiers = [[FK Sloga Jugomagnat|Sloga Jugomagnat]]\n| continentalcup3  = [[1997\u201398 UEFA Cup|UEFA Cup]]\n| continentalcup3 qualifiers = [[FK Pobeda|Pobeda]]\n| league topscorer = [[Miroslav Gjoki\u0107]]<br />(16 goals)\n| dates            = 16 August 1996 \u2013<br /> 1 June 1997<ref name=\"First\">[http://fudbalforum.com/index.php?threads/macedonian-league-in-the-past-%D0%9C%D0%B0%D0%BA%D0%B5%D0%B4%D0%BE%D0%BD%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%B0%D1%82%D0%B0-%D0%9B%D0%B8%D0%B3%D0%B0-%D0%B2%D0%BE-%D0%BC%D0%B8%D0%BD%D0%B0%D1%82%D0%BE%D1%82%D0%BE.457/page-29#post-182741]</ref>\n| biggest home win = [[FK Sileks|Sileks]] 17\u20131 [[FK Rudar Probi\u0161tip|Rudar]]\n| biggest away win = [[FK Rudar Probi\u0161tip|Rudar]] 1\u20137 [[GFK Tikvesh|Tikvesh]]\n| highest scoring  = [[FK Sileks|Sileks]] 17\u20131 [[FK Rudar Probi\u0161tip|Rudar]]\n| matches          = 182\n| total goals      = 522\n| prevseason = [[1995\u201396 Macedonian First Football League|1995\u201396]]\n| nextseason = [[1997\u201398 Macedonian First Football League|1997\u201398]]\n}}\n\nThe '''1996\u201397 Macedonian First League''' was the 5th season of the [[Macedonian First Football League]], the highest [[Association football|football]] league of [[North Macedonia|Macedonia]]. The first matches of the season were played on 16 August 1996 and the last on 1 June 1997.<ref name=\"First\" /> [[FK Sileks|Sileks]] defended their championship title, having won their second title in a row.\n\n== Promotion and relegation ==\n{|style=\"border:0;width:69%;\"\n|-style=\"vertical-align:top;\"\n|\n; At the start of the 1996\u201397 season\nPromoted from [[1995\u201396 Macedonian Second Football League|1995\u201396 Second League]]\n* [[KF Shk\u00ebndija|Shk\u00ebndija]] (Winners; West)\n* [[FK Bregalnica \u0160tip|Bregalnica Shtip]] (Winners; East)\nRelegated to [[1996\u201397 Macedonian Second Football League|1996\u201397 Second League]]\n* [[FK Ohrid|Ohrid]] (13th)\n* [[FK Osogovo|Osogovo]] (14th)\n* [[FK Ljuboten|Ljuboten]] (15th)\n\n|\n; At the end of the 1996\u201397 season\nPromoted from [[1996\u201397 Macedonian Second Football League|1996\u201397 Second League]]\n* [[FK Skopje|Skopje]] (Winners; West)\n* [[FK Borec|Borec]] (Winners; East)\nRelegated to [[1997\u201398 Macedonian Second Football League|1997\u201398 Second League]]\n* [[KF Shk\u00ebndija|Shk\u00ebndija]] (13th)\n* [[FK Rudar Probi\u0161tip|Rudar Probishtip]] (14th)\n|}\n\n== Participating teams ==\n{{Location map+|Republic of Macedonia|float=right|width=400|caption=Location of teams in '''1996\u201397 Macedonian First League'''|places=\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42        |long=21.433333 |label='''Skopje'''  |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.031944 |long=21.334722 |label=[[FK Pelister|Pelister]] }}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.35     |long=21.55     |label=[[FK Pobeda|Pobeda]] }}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.733333 |long=22.183333 |label=[[FK Bregalnica \u0160tip|Bregalnica]] |position=right}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42        |long=22.15     |label=[[FK Rudar Probi\u0161tip|Rudar]] |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42.019722 |long=22.591667 |label=[[FK Sasa|Sasa]] |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.433333 |long=22.633333 |label=[[FK Belasica|Belasica]] |position=left}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42.066667 |long=22.183333 |label=[[FK Sileks|Sileks]] }}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.433333 |long=22        |label=[[GFK Tikvesh|Tikvesh]] |position=top}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42        |long=20.966666 |label=[[KF Shk\u00ebndija|Shk\u00ebndija]] |position=bottom}}\n<!--HIDDEN MARKER FOR SKOPJE CLUBS (UPPER RIGHT CORNER)-->\n{{Location map~ |Republic of Macedonia|mark=TransparentPlaceholder.png|lat=42.44 |long=23.2 |label='''Skopje&nbsp;clubs:'''|position=left | outside  = 1 <!-- Turn off error category due to location outside map-->}}\n{{Location map~ |Republic of Macedonia|mark=TransparentPlaceholder.png|lat=42.36 |long=23.2 |label=[[FK Balkan Skopje|Balkan]]<br>[[FK Cementarnica 55|Cementarnica]]<br>[[FK Makedonija Gjor\u010de Petrov|Makedonija]]<br>[[FK Sloga Jugomagnat|Sloga Jugomagnat]]<br>[[FK Vardar|Vardar]] |position=left | outside  = 1 <!-- Turn off error category due to location outside map-->}}\n}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Club\n! City\n! Stadium\n|-\n| [[FK Balkan Skopje|Balkan BISI]]\n| [[Skopje]]\n| [[\u010cair Stadium (North Macedonia)|Chair Stadium]]\n|-\n| [[FK Belasica|Belasica]]\n| [[Strumica]]\n| [[Stadion Blagoj Istatov|Stadion Mladost]]\n|-\n| [[FK Bregalnica \u0160tip|Bregalnica]]\n| [[\u0160tip|Shtip]]\n| [[Gradski stadion \u0160tip|Gradski stadion Shtip]]\n|-\n| [[FK Cementarnica 55|Cementarnica 55]]\n| [[Skopje]]\n| [[Cementarnica Stadium|Stadion Cementarnica]]\n|-\n| [[FK Makedonija Gjor\u010de Petrov|Makedonija]]\n| [[Skopje]]\n| [[Gjor\u010de Petrov Stadium|Stadion Gjorche Petrov]]\n|-\n| [[FK Pelister|Pelister]]\n| [[Bitola]]\n| [[Stadion Tumbe Kafe]]\n|-\n| [[FK Pobeda|Pobeda]]\n| [[Prilep]]\n| [[Stadion Goce Del\u010dev|Stadion Goce Delchev]]\n|-\n| [[FK Rudar Probi\u0161tip|Rudar]]\n| [[Probi\u0161tip|Probishtip]]\n| Gradski stadion Probishtip\n|- \n| [[FK Sasa|Sasa]]\n| [[Makedonska Kamenica]]\n| Gradski stadion Makedonska Kamenica\n|-\n| [[KF Shk\u00ebndija|Shk\