Prohibition]]\n| [[Earl Dodge]] <small>(Write-In)</small>\n| align=\"right\" | 2\n| align=\"right\" | <0.01%\n| align=\"right\" | 0\n|-\n|-bgcolor=\"#EEEEEE\"\n| colspan=\"3\" align=\"right\" | '''Totals'''\n| align=\"right\" | '''2,773,574'''\n| align=\"right\" | '''100.0%'''\n| align=\"right\" | '''12'''\n|}\n(a) [[Howard Phillips (politician)|Howard Phillips]] was the candidate of the [[Constitution Party (United States)|U.S. Taxpayers' Party]] nationally.\n\n===Results by Congressional district===\nClinton won all 11 Congressional districts.\n{|class=wikitable\n! District\n! Bush\n! Clinton\n! Perot\n! Representative\n|- align=center\n! {{party shading/Democratic}}|{{ushr|Massachusetts|1|1st}}\n| 27%\n| '''48%'''\n| 25%\n| {{party shading/Democratic}}|[[John Olver]]\n|- align=center\n! {{party shading/Democratic}}|{{ushr|Massachusetts|2|2nd}}\n| 29%\n| '''46%'''\n| 25%\n| {{party shading/Democratic}}|[[Richard Neal]]\n|- align=center\n! rowspan=2 {{party shading/Democratic}}|{{ushr|Massachusetts|3|3rd}}\n| rowspan=2|31%\n| rowspan=2|'''45%'''\n| rowspan=2|23%\n| {{party shading/Democratic}}|[[Joseph D. Early]]\n|- align=center\n| {{party shading/Republican}}|[[Peter I. Blute]]\n|- align=center\n! {{party shading/Democratic}}|{{ushr|Massachusetts|4|4th}}\n| 26%\n| '''51%'''\n| 22%\n| {{party shading/Democratic}}|[[Barney Frank]]\n|- align=center\n! rowspan=2 {{party shading/Democratic}}|{{ushr|Massachusetts|5|5th}}\n| rowspan=2|32%\n| rowspan=2|'''42%'''\n| rowspan=2|26%\n| {{party shading/Democratic}}|[[Chester G. Atkins]]\n|- align=center\n| {{party shading/Democratic}}|[[Marty Meehan]]\n|- align=center\n! rowspan=2 {{party shading/Democratic}}|{{ushr|Massachusetts|6|6th}}\n| rowspan=2|31%\n| rowspan=2|'''44%'''\n| rowspan=2|25%\n| {{party shading/Democratic}}|[[Nicholas Mavroules]]\n|- align=center\n| {{party shading/Republican}}|[[Peter G. Torkildsen]]\n|- align=center\n! {{party shading/Democratic}}|{{ushr|Massachusetts|7|7th}}\n| 29%\n| '''50%'''\n| 21%\n| 