, 1992}}\n[[Category:1992 United States presidential election by state|Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:United States presidential elections in Massachusetts|1992]]\n[[Category:1992 Massachusetts elections]]\n", "name_user": "MyPreferredUsernameWasTaken", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1992_United_States_presidential_election_in_Massachusetts"}
{"title_page": "1995\u201396 Macedonian First Football League", "text_new": "{{Infobox football league season\n| competition      = Macedonian First League\n| season           = 1995\u201396\n| winners          = [[FK Sileks|Sileks]]<br />1st domestic title\n| relegated        = [[FK Ohrid|Ohrid]]<br />[[FK Osogovo|Osogovo]]<br />[[FK Ljuboten|Ljuboten]]\n| continentalcup1  = [[1996\u201397 UEFA Cup|UEFA Cup]]\n| continentalcup1 qualifiers = [[FK Sileks|Sileks]]<br />[[FK Vardar|Vardar]]\n| continentalcup2  = [[1996\u201397 UEFA Cup Winners' Cup|Cup Winners' Cup]]\n| continentalcup2 qualifiers = [[FK Sloga Jugomagnat|Sloga Jugomagnat]]\n| league topscorer = [[Zoran Bo\u0161kovski|Zoran Boshkovski]]<br />(20 goals)\n| dates            = 20 August 1995 \u2013<br /> 9 June 1996<ref name=\"First\">[http://fudbalforum.com/index.php?threads/macedonian-league-in-the-past-%D0%9C%D0%B0%D0%BA%D0%B5%D0%B4%D0%BE%D0%BD%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%B0%D1%82%D0%B0-%D0%9B%D0%B8%D0%B3%D0%B0-%D0%B2%D0%BE-%D0%BC%D0%B8%D0%BD%D0%B0%D1%82%D0%BE%D1%82%D0%BE.457/page-25#post-180716]</ref>\n| biggest home win = [[FK Sileks|Sileks]] 10\u20130 [[FK Ljuboten|Ljuboten]]\n| biggest away win = [[FK Rudar Probi\u0161tip|Rudar]] 0\u20135 [[FK Vardar|Vardar]]\n| highest scoring  = [[FK Sileks|Sileks]] 10\u20130 [[FK Ljuboten|Ljuboten]]\n| matches          = 210\n| total goals      = 615\n| prevseason = [[1994\u201395 Macedonian First Football League|1994\u201395]]\n| nextseason = [[1996\u201397 Macedonian First Football League|1996\u201397]]\n}}\n\nThe '''1995\u201396 Macedonian First League''' was the 4th season of the [[Macedonian First Football League]], the highest [[Association football|football]] league of [[North Macedonia|Macedonia]]. The first matches of the season were played on 20 August 1995 and the last on 9 June 1996.<ref name=\"First\" /> [[FK Vardar|Vardar]] were the defending champions, having won their third title in a row. The 1995-96 champions were [[FK Sileks]] who had won their first title.\n\n== Promotion and relegation ==\n{|style=\"border:0;width:69%;\"\n|-style=\"vertical-align:top;\"\n|\n; At the start of the 1995\u201396 season\nPromoted from [[1994\u201395 Macedonian Second Football League|1994\u201395 Second League]]\n* [[FK Makedonija Gjor\u010de Petrov|Makedonija Skopje]] (Winners; West)\n* ''[[FK Pobeda Valandovo|Pobeda Valandovo]] (Winners; East)''<sup>1</sup>\nRelegated to [[1995\u201396 Macedonian Second Football League|1995\u201396 Second League]]\n* [[FK Borec|Borec]] (15th)\n* [[FK Ko\u017euf|Kozhuf Vinojug]] (16th)\n\n|\n; At the end of the 1995\u201396 season\nPromoted from [[1995\u201396 Macedonian Second Football League|1995\u201396 Second League]]\n* [[KF Shk\u00ebndija|Shk\u00ebndija]] (Winners; West)\n* [[FK Bregalnica \u0160tip|Bregalnica Shtip]] (Winners; East)\nRelegated to [[1996\u201397 Macedonian Second Football League|1996\u201397 Second League]]\n* [[FK Ohrid|Ohrid]] (13th)\n* [[FK Osogovo|Osogovo]] (14th)\n* [[FK Ljuboten|Ljuboten]] (15th)\n|}\n1 Pobeda Valandovo was initially promoted, but was expelled from the First League due to unknown reasons.\n\n== Participating teams ==\n{{Location map+|Republic of Macedonia|float=right|width=400|caption=Location of teams in '''1995\u201396 Macedonian First League'''|places=\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42        |long=21.433333 |label='''Skopje'''  |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.031944 |long=21.334722 |label=[[FK Pelister|Pelister]] }}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.35     |long=21.55     |label=[[FK Pobeda|Pobeda]] }}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42        |long=22.15     |label=[[FK Rudar Probi\u0161tip|Rudar]] |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.916667 |long=22.416667 |label=[[FK Osogovo|Osogovo]] |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42.019722 |long=22.591667 |label=[[FK Sasa|Sasa]] |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.